trans-unit.source: Defines a compiler that is used to support the compilation infrastructure of Web applications.
This class cannot be inherited.
The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.Compiler> class provides a way to programmatically access a compiler configuration element.
Creates an instance of a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.Compiler"></xref> initialized to the provided values.
Lists additional compiler-specific options to pass during compilation.
Provides a semicolon-separated list of file-name extensions used for dynamic code-behind files.
For example, ".cs".
Provides a semicolon-separated list of languages used in dynamic compilation files.
For example, "c#;cs;csharp".
Specifies a comma-separated class/assembly combination that indicates the .NET Framework class.
Specifies compiler warning levels.
Gets a list of compiler-specific options to use during compilation.
A value specifying the compiler-specific options to use during compilation.
This is not a merged set but rather overrides any previously defined values in earlier configuration entries.
Gets a list of file-name extensions used for dynamic code-behind files.
When the list of file-name extensions includes more than one extension, the list is semicolon-separated.
A value specifying the file-name extensions used for dynamic code-behind files, files in the code directory, and other referenced files.
Gets a list of programming languages to use in dynamic compilation files.
When the list of programming languages includes more than one language, the list is semicolon-separated.
A value specifying the programming languages to use in dynamic compilation files.
Gets the compiler type name of the language provider for dynamic compilation files.
Specifies the type name of the language provider, including the name of the assembly containing the provider implementation.
A value specifying the type name of the language compiler to use in dynamic compilation files.
Gets the compiler warning level.
Specifies the default compiler warning level; determines the level at which the language provider treats compilation warnings as errors.
A value specifying the compiler warning level.
